page.title: 01Carnach, Killilan
page.content:
Carnach consists of one house and outbuilding and a derelict small shooting lodge. About a mile further along the road east is Duilleach which also has one house and outbuilding. Both in a state of disrepair.
Behind these houses rise the mountains covered with heather, bracken and rough grazing. Red and roe deer, sheep and highland cattle graze here. Buzzard and Golden Eagle can be seen.
There are a few small hill lochs where brown trout breed. They are also found in the river Elchaig which lies to the south east.
